|} 

On September 5, [[Kv<U+011B>ta Peschke]] and [[Katarina Srebotnik]] became the first doubles team to qualify for the year-end championships.<ref name="first qualifiers"/>

'''Kv<U+011B>ta Peschke''' and '''Katarina Srebotnik''' continued their partnership coming to 2011, they also were able to reach the no. 1 ranking in doubles for the first time on July 4, 2011. They were also able to win 6 titles together their first coming in the [[2011 ASB Classic|ASB Classic]] over the team of [[Sofia Arvidsson|Arvidsson]] & [[Marina Erakovic|Erakovic]] 6<U+2013>3, 6<U+2013>0. They then won their second title in the [[2011 Qatar Ladies Open|Qatar Ladies Open]] over [[Liezel Huber|Huber]] & [[Nadia Petrova|Petrova]] 7<U+2013>5, 6<U+2013>7<sup>(2<U+2013>7)</sup>, [10<U+2013>8]. Their next titles came in back-to-back-to-back winning in [[2011 Aegon International|Aegon International]] over Huber & [[Lisa Raymond|Raymond]] 6<U+2013>3, 6<U+2013>0, in [[2011 Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon]] over [[Sabine Lisicki|Lisicki]] & [[Samantha Stosur|Stosur]] 6<U+2013>3, 6<U+2013>1 and in the [[2011 Mercury Insurance Open|Mercury Insurance Open]] over [[Raquel Kops-Jones|Kopz-Jones]] & [[Abigail Spears|Spears]] 6<U+2013>0, 6<U+2013>2. Their triumph in Wimbledon is the team's first Slam title together and their first as individuals in the women's doubles. They then claimed their sixth title at the [[2011 China Open (tennis)|China Open]] over [[Gisela Dulko|Dulko]] & [[Flavia Pennetta|Pennetta]] 6<U+2013>3, 6<U+2013>4. They also reached three other finals in the [[2011 Medibank International Sydney|Medibank International Sydney]] losing to [[Iveta Bene<U+0161>ov<U+00E1>|Bene<U+0161>ov<U+00E1>]] & [[Barbora Z<U+00E1>hlavov<U+00E1>-Str<U+00FD>cov<U+00E1>|Z<U+00E1>hlavov<U+00E1>-Str<U+00FD>cov<U+00E1>]], in [[2011 Dubai Tennis Championships|Dubai Tennis Championships]] falling to Huber & [[Mar<U+00ED>a Jos<U+00E9> Mart<U+00ED>nez S<U+00E1>nchez|Mart<U+00ED>nez S<U+00E1>nchez]] and in the [[2011 Mutua Madrid Open|Mutua Madrid Open]] to [[Victoria Azarenka|Azarenka]] & [[Maria Kirilenko|Kirilenko]]. Srebotnik also on the mixed doubles title in the [[2011 Australian Open|Australian Open]] with [[Daniel Nestor]]. In the other Slams they were able to reach the semifinals of the Australian Open and the quarterfinals of the [[2011 French Open|French Open]] and [[2011 US Open (tennis)|US Open]].

On October 1, [[Liezel Huber]] and [[Lisa Raymond]] became the second team to qualify for the championships.<ref name="second qualifiers"/>

'''Liezel Huber''' and '''Lisa Raymond''' did not start pairing up for doubles until the European clay season as Huber initially paired with [[Nadia Petrova]] and Raymond teamed up with [[Julia G<U+00F6>rges]]. The veteran team then had a great result together, reaching the semifinals of the [[2011 French Open|French Open]] and the quarterfinals of [[2011 Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon]]. They lost their first two finals in the [[2011 Aegon International|Aegon International]] losing to [[Kv<U+011B>ta Peschke|Peschke]] & [[Katarina Srebotnik|Srebotnik]] 6<U+2013>3, 6<U+2013>0 and in the [[2011 Bank of the West Classic|Bank of the West Classic]] losing to Azarenka & Kirilenko 6<U+2013>1, 6<U+2013>3. Their first title as a team came in as a gift winning the [[2011 Rogers Cup|Rogers Cup]] over Azarenka & Kirilenko in a walkover. They then claim their first Slam as a team in the [[2011 US Open (tennis)|US Open]] over [[Vania King|King]] & [[Yaroslava Shvedova|Shvedova]] 4<U+2013>6, 7<U+2013>6<sup>(7<U+2013>5)</sup>, 7<U+2013>6<sup>(7<U+2013>3)</sup>. They then collected their third title at the [[2011 Toray Pan Pacific Open|Toray Pan Pacific Open]] over Dulko & Pennetta 7<U+2013>6<sup>(7<U+2013>4)</sup>, 0<U+2013>6, [10<U+2013>6]. Huber was also able reach two other finals in the [[2011 Dubai Tennis Championships|Dubai Tennis Championships]] with [[Mar<U+00ED>a Jos<U+00E9> Mart<U+00ED>nez S<U+00E1>nchez]] winning over Peschke & Srebotnik 7<U+2013>6<sup>(7<U+2013>5)</sup>, 6<U+2013>3 and in the [[2011 Qatar Ladies Open|Qatar Ladies Open]] with [[Nadia Petrova]] in a losing effort to Peschke & Srebotnik.

On October 11, [[Gisela Dulko]] and [[Flavia Pennetta]] became the third team to qualify for the championships.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wtachampionships.com/page/LatestNews/Read/0,,12910~2478974,00.html |title='Dulko and Penetta to Defend Year-End Title' |publisher=Wtachampionships.com |date=2011-10-11 |accessdate=2011-10-30}}</ref>

'''Gisela Dulko''' and '''Flavia Penetta''' failed to duplicate their 2010 season winning 6 titles and the championship as they only won one title in the year, but it is their most prestigious  title as a team this coming in the [[2011 Australian Open|Australian Open]] beating [[Victoria Azarenka|Azarenka]] & [[Maria Kirilenko|Kirilenko]] 2<U+2013>6, 7<U+2013>5, 6<U+2013>1. This marks their first Slam title as team and as individuals. An injury suffered by Dulko prevented the team to collect some points during the mid-season. However, the team performed well during the Asian swing and became the runner-up in both [[2011 Toray Pan Pacific Open|Toray Pan Pacific Open]] to [[Liezel Huber|Huber]] & [[Lisa Raymond|Raymond]] and [[2011 China Open (tennis)|China Open]] to [[Kv<U+011B>ta Peschke|Peschke]] & [[Katarina Srebotnik|Srebotnik]]. In the other Slams they reached the quarterfinals of the [[2011 French Open|French Open]] and the third round of the [[2011 US Open (tennis)|US Open]]. Pennetta also reached another final with [[Dominika Cibulkov<U+00E1>]] at the [[2011 UNICEF Open|UNICEF Open]] losing to [[Barbora Z<U+00E1>hlavov<U+00E1>-Str<U+00FD>cov<U+00E1>|Z<U+00E1>hlavov<U+00E1>-Str<U+00FD>cov<U+00E1>]] & [[Kl<U+00E1>ra Zakopalov<U+00E1>|Zakopalov<U+00E1>]].

On October 16, [[Vania King]] and [[Yaroslava Shvedova]] took the last spot over [[Victoria Azarenka]] and [[Maria Kirilenko]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wtachampionships.com/page/LatestNews/Read/0,,12910~2484261,00.html |title=Vania & Slava Complete Istanbul Doubles Field |publisher=Wtachampionships.com |date=2011-10-16 |accessdate=2011-10-30}}</ref>

'''Vania King and Yaroslava Shvedova''' wasn't able to play together until the [[2011 BNP Paribas Open|BNP Paribas Open]] due to Shvedova's knee injury. The team weren't able to match up to their 2010 season when they won 2 Slam titles, as they only reached 1 slam final in the [[2011 US Open (tennis)|US Open]] losing to [[Liezel Huber|Huber]] & [[Lisa Raymond|Raymond]] 6<U+2013>4, 6<U+2013>7<sup>(5<U+2013>7)</sup>, 6<U+2013>7<sup>(3<U+2013>7)</sup>. They won their first title of the year at the [[2011 Western & Southern Open|Western & Southern Open]] winning 6<U+2013>4, 3<U+2013>6, [11<U+2013>9] over [[Natalie Grandin|Grandin]] & [[Vladim<U+00ED>ra Uhl<U+00ED><U+0159>ov<U+00E1>|Uhl<U+00ED><U+0159>ov<U+00E1>]]. They also reached two other finals in a losing effort in the [[2011 Internazionali BNL d'Italia|Internazionali BNL d'Italia]] losing to the Chinese pair of [[Peng Shuai|Peng]] & [[Zheng Jie|Zheng]] 2<U+2013>6, 3<U+2013>6 and in the [[2011 HP Open|HP Open]] losing to the Asian pair of [[Kimiko Date-Krumm|Date-Krumm]] & [[Zhang Shuai (tennis)|Zhang]] in the final 5<U+2013>7, 6<U+2013>3, [9<U+2013>11]. Shvedova was able to win another title with [[Sania Mirza]] this time at the [[2011 Citi Open|Citi Open]] over [[Olga Govortsova|Govortsova]] & [[Alla Kudryavtseva|Kudryavtseva]] 6<U+2013>3, 6<U+2013>3. King also reached a final with a different partner [[Anna-Lena Gr<U+00F6>nefeld]] at the [[2011 Monterrey Open|Monterrey Open]] losing to Czechs [[Iveta Bene<U+0161>ov<U+00E1>|Bene<U+0161>ov<U+00E1>]] & [[Barbora Z<U+00E1>hlavov<U+00E1>-Str<U+00FD>cov<U+00E1>|Z<U+00E1>hlavov<U+00E1>-Str<U+00FD>cov<U+00E1>]].

==Groupings==
<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wtatennis.com/page/HeadToHeadIntro/0,,12781,00.html |title=Head to Head |publisher=Wtatennis.com |date= |accessdate=2011-10-30}}</ref>
The 2011 edition of the year-end championships featured two former World number ones, four Grand Slam champions, two Grand Slam finalists. Two of them made their debut at the championships. The competitors were divided into two groups representing the colors of the [[flag of Turkey]]. The Red group consisted of no. 1 seed Caroline Wozniacki, no. 3 seed Petra Kvitov<U+00E1>, no. 6 seed Vera Zvonareva and no. 8 seed Agnieszka Radwa<U+0144>ska. The White Group was composed of no. 2 seed Maria Sharapova, no, 4 seed Victoria Azarenka, no. 5 seed Li Na and no. 7 seed Samantha Stosur.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wtatennis.com/SEWTATour-Archive/posting/2011/808/MDS.pdf |title=WTA Championships 2011 <U+2013> Draw |author= |date=October 23, 2011 |work=WTA Tour website|publisher= |format=PDF|accessdate=October 24, 2011}}</ref> Marion Bartoli and Andrea Petkovic served as alternates.

In the red group, in their respective records in their group, World no. 1 [[Caroline Wozniacki]] was 11<U+2013>6, [[Petra Kvitov<U+00E1>]] was 5<U+2013>6, [[Vera Zvonareva]] was 9<U+2013>9 and [[Agnieszka Radwa<U+0144>ska]] was 4<U+2013>8. Leading the group Wozniacki, has a good record in each opponent in her group. She has a positive record against Kvitov<U+00E1>, leading the Wimbledon champion 3<U+2013>1, with their last meeting coming in the third round of the [[2010 China Open (tennis)|2010 China Open]], with Wozniacki winning 6<U+2013>3, 6<U+2013>2 and all their matches were won in straight sets. Against Zvonareva, she has a record of 4<U+2013>4, with Zvonareva winning their only encounter in 2011 in the final of the [[2011 Qatar Ladies Open|Qatar Ladies Open]] 6<U+2013>4, 6<U+2013>4. Against good friend Radwa<U+0144>ska, the Dane lead 4<U+2013>1 winning their last four matches including their only encounter in 2011 at the semifinal of the [[2011 Porsche Tennis Grand Prix|Porsche Tennis Grand Prix]] 7<U+2013>5, 6<U+2013>3, with Radwa<U+0144>ska's last win coming in 2007. Zvonareva on the other hand, has close records against Kvitov<U+00E1> and Radwa<U+0144>ska. Against Kvitov<U+00E1>, the Russian leads 3<U+2013>2 facing each other 3 times in 2011 all won in straight sets, with Zvonerva winning two of them in the quarterfinals of the [[2011 Australian Open|Australian Open]] and the semifinal of the [[2011 Toray Pan Pacific Open|Toray Pan Pacific Open]] and lost in the third round of the [[2011 Mutua Madrid Open|Mutua Madrid Open]]. In her match-up against Radwa<U+0144>ska, the Russian trails 2<U+2013>3 with them competing against each other 4 times in 2011 all won in straight sets and the Pole winning their last three encounters <U+2013> the first in the final of [[2011 Mercury Insurance Open|Mercury Insurance Open]], the third round of [[2011 Rogers Cup|Rogers Cup]], and the final of the [[2011 Toray Pan Pacific Open|Toray Pan Pacific Open]], Zvonerva's last win came in quarterfinal of the [[2011 Sony Ericsson Open|Sony Ericsson Open]]. In the head-to-head of first time qualifiers. Kvitov<U+00E1> and Radwa<U+0144>ska, The Czech has won both of their matches including their last match in the quarterfinal of [[2011 Aegon International|Aegon International]] 1<U+2013>6, 6<U+2013>2, 7<U+2013>6<sup>(7<U+2013>2)</sup> 

In the white group, in their head-to-heads with players within their group, [[Maria Sharapova]] was 17<U+2013>6, [[Victoria Azarenka]] was 8<U+2013>7, [[Li Na (tennis)|Li Na]] was 7<U+2013>11, and [[Samantha Stosur]] was 5<U+2013>13. Like Wozniacki, Sharapova has a good record against each members of her group. Against Azarenka, they have split their match-ups with each having 3 wins, and also splitting their match-ups in 2011 with 1 win each, with Azarenka winning in the final of the [[2011 Sony Ericsson Open|Sony Ericsson Open]] and Sharapova winning in the quarterfinal of the [[2011 Internazionali BNL d'Italia|Internazionali BNL d'Italia]]. Against Li, Sharapova leads their head-to-head 5<U+2013>3, however Li has won their 3 previous meetings in straight sets including the semifinal of the [[2011 French Open|French Open]] 6<U+2013>4, 7<U+2013>5. Against Stosur, Sharapova has a perfect record of 9<U+2013>0 including 3 straight set wins in the fourth round of the [[2011 Sony Ericsson Open|Sony Ericsson Open]], the final of the [[2011 Internazionali BNL d'Italia|Internazionali BNL d'Italia]], and the quarterfinal of the [[2011 Western & Southern Open|Western & Southern Open]]. Azarenka, in the other hand has a mixed record against Li and Stosur. She trails Li 1<U+2013>4, including losing in the fourth round of the [[2011 Australian Open|Australian Open]] 6<U+2013>3, 6<U+2013>3 and the quarterfinal of the [[2011 French Open|French Open]] 7<U+2013>5, 6<U+2013>2. However, against Stosur, Azarenka has never lost a match and a set winning their four encounters, with their last meeting coming in semifinal of the [[2010 Bank of the West Classic]] with the Belorussian winning 6<U+2013>2, 6<U+2013>3. In the match-up between Slam champions Li and Stosur, despite Stosur having lost all matches against Sharapova and Azarenka, she has never lost to Li winning their 5 matches including 3 in 2011 in the semifinal of the [[2011 Internazionali BNL d'Italia|Internazionali BNL d'Italia]], the third rounds of [[2011 Rogers Cup|Rogers Cup]] and [[2011 Western & Southern Open|Western & Southern Open]].

The four doubles teams started the semifinals without group play.

